node.text:
Would you try this? 😳💦

Devil’s Pool is a natural pool of water that’s situated atop of Victoria Falls, renown for being among the largest waterfalls in the world. Right on the edge of this massive waterfall, a calm pool of water forms.

This is known as the Devil’s Pool Victoria Falls. And daring visitors can actually swim in this pool straddling the edge of Victoria Falls!

📽 @abenafrica
📍Zambia and Zimbabwe
🎶 Ikson - Apart

node.text:
The Land of Legends in Turkey 😍 Unleash your adventurous spirit at Turkey’s first magical kingdom. Packed to the brim with entertainment to suit any taste, a holiday here ensures a legendary and unforgettable experience for all the family. From the on-site theme park to the Venetian-style canals, the Land of Legends is sure to live up to its name.

📽 @waelalteen
📍Antalya, Turkey
🎶 Hailey Barnes & Calvin Jenkins - Lovely

node.text:
Hey little guy! @animaledventures show us the pouch, that acts as a warm, safe place for joeys. 🙏🏽

At around six months, when a baby kangaroo is sufficiently well developed, it will leave the pouch for short periods, returning when it needs to feed. Did you know that?

📽 @animaledventures

📷 @henry_do
📍Copenhagen, Dennmark

node.text:
Hagia Sophia 🤩 (Ayasofya in Turkish) can be considered as the best and the most visited sights in #Istanbul together with the neighboring Topkapi Palace.
It is a former church and museum and declared as one of the world’s greatest architectural works.

Built as a church in 325, Hagia Sophia was rebuilt in 537 and was converted into a mosque by Fatih Sultan Mehmet after the conquest of Istanbul in 1453.
In 1935, the Hagia Sophia was established as a museum under Mustafa Kemal Ataturk and the newly established secular republic of Turkey.

Last July, the Turkish government opened Hagia Sophia to prayer for the first time in 86 years, reverting the building’s status from museum back to mosque.

📸 1-4. @thehakanarslan, 5. @dr.iyasar
